You have a classical problem of **remove an item from the single linked list**. This is not depend on the item&#39;s data.

You should define a class of the container. And internal item representation (a node with data and reference to the next node). And finally implement the delete method.

How to delete a randome method from the single linked list:

 1. Find the item (e.g. `A`).
 1. Find the previous item (e.g. `preA`)
 1. Find the next item (e.g. `nextA`)
 1. Change reference from `preA -&gt; A` to `preA -&gt; nextA`
 1. Remove reference `A -&gt; null`

So your container could look like this:
```java
public final class SinglyLinkedList&lt;T&gt; {

    private Node&lt;T&gt; head;

    public void add(T data) {
        if (head == null)
            head = new Node&lt;&gt;(data);
        else {
            Node&lt;T&gt; node = head;

            while (node.next != null)
                node = node.next;

            node.next = new Node&lt;&gt;(data);
        }
    }

    @RequiredArgsConstructor
    private static final class Node&lt;T&gt; {

        private final T data;
        private Node&lt;T&gt; next;

    }

}
```

And then, e.g. in case you want to remove every `2nd` element, then it could look like this:
```java
public List&lt;T&gt; removeEvenItems() {
    if (head == null || head.next == null)
        return List.of();

    boolean remove = false;
    Node&lt;T&gt; prv = null;
    Node&lt;T&gt; node = head;
    List&lt;T&gt; removed = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();

    while (node != null) {
        if (remove) {
            removed.add(node.data);
            prv.next = node.next;
            node.next = null;
            node = prv.next;
        } else {
            prv = node;
            node = node.next;
        }

        remove = !remove;
    }

    return removed;
}
```

Or remove every `1st` elements:

```java
public List&lt;T&gt; removeOddItems() {
    if (head == null)
        return List.of();

    if (head.next == null) {
        T data = head.data;
        head = null;
        return List.of(data);
    }

    boolean remove = true;
    Node&lt;T&gt; prv = null;
    Node&lt;T&gt; node = head;
    List&lt;T&gt; removed = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();

    while (node != null) {
        if (remove) {
            removed.add(node.data);

            if (prv == null) {
                head = node.next;
                node.next = null;
                node = head;
            } else {
                prv.next = node.next;
                node.next = null;
                node = prv.next;
            }
        } else {
            prv = node;
            node = node.next;
        }

        remove = !remove;
    }

    return removed;
}
```

