answers.body_markdown:
The inner for loop `for(int row = startNum; row &lt;= o; row++)` does `o - startNum + 1` iterations, when in reality it needs to do `o` iterations. Your code works for the case of `1` because `o - startNum + 1` is equal to `o` when `startNum` is equal to 1. 

Changing your code to the following should solve your problem:

```
for (int o = startNum; o &lt;= endNum; o++) {
    for(int row = 1; row &lt;= o; row++) {
        System.out.print(o + &quot;&quot;);
    }
    System.out.println(&quot;&quot;);
}    
```

